\item  

Once you have finished implementing the code gaps, proceed with the following sub-parts:

\begin{enumerate}[label=\roman*.]

    \item \points{2ci} Run the RL fine-tuning with

        \begin{tcolorbox}[width=\linewidth, sharp corners=all, colback=white!95!black]
        \begin{verbatim}
        python train.py agent.num_critics=2 utd=1
        \end{verbatim}
        \end{tcolorbox}

    \item \points{2cii} Attach the plot ``eval/episode\_success" for the above run from Tensorboard. You should achieve a success rate of at least 90\% before 100K environment steps.

